  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6511.44 sitting right between the massive negative gamma wall at 6475 (-6.2B) and positive gamma at 6525 (+1.6B), dealers are currently in flow-dependent mode but leaning toward selling pressure as we approach the 6515 resistance (-3.5B GEX). The BREAKOUT regime with -4.1B total GEX means dealers will amplify any directional move - if we break below 6500, expect accelerated selling into the 6475 monster wall, while a push above 6525 flips dealers to stabilizing mode where they'll fade moves.\n\nKey inflection point is 6525 - above this level dealers switch from amplifying to dampening volatility, but failure here likely triggers dealer selling back toward 6500-6475 zone where the heaviest negative gamma sits.",
